080`\n- `COMMODITY_STYLE_NO_MIGRATE 0x2000`\n- `COMMODITY_PRECISION_FROM_PRICE 0x8000`\n\nThe precedent for this pattern is in `src/pool.cc` lines 359-365:\n```cpp\nif (point.price.has_commodity()) {\n    commodity_t& price_commodity = point.price.commodity();\n    if (price_commodity.precision() == 0 && !price_commodity.has_flags(COMMODITY_KNOWN) &&\n        !price_commodity.has_flags(COMMODITY_STYLE_NO_MIGRATE)) {\n      price_commodity.set_precision(point.price.precision());\n      price_commodity.add_flags(COMMODITY_PRECISION_FROM_PRICE);\n    }\n  }\n```\n\n## Task\n\n1. **Fix `src/py_commodity.cc`**: Modify `py_exchange_2` and `py_exchange_3` to add `COMMODITY_PRECISION_FROM_PRICE` to the per_unit_cost commodity after calling `pool.exchange()`. The condition should mirror `parse_price_directive`: add the flag if the commodity is not `COMMODITY_KNOWN` and not `COMMODITY_STYLE_NO_MIGRATE`. Unlike `parse_price_directive`, don't check for `precision() == 0` since the precision may already be set by the Amount creation.\n\n2. **Create `test/regress/1019.py`**: A Python test that:\n   - Sets up `comms.exchange(comms.find_or_create('Nectar'), ledger.Amount('0.005 GBP'))`\n   - Reads a journal from string that includes a transaction requiring 2-decimal GBP precision to balance\n   - The test demonstrates the fix works (no \"Transaction does not balance\" error)\n   \n   The transaction that triggers the bug:\n   ```\n   2014-01-01 Test\n       A  -1.40 USD @ (1/1.578 GBP)\n       B   0.89 GBP\n   ```\n   With GBP precision 3 (bug): -1.40/1.578 rounds to -0.887 GBP, remainder = 0.89 - 0.887 = 0.003 GBP → ERROR\n   With GBP precision 2 (fix): -1.40/1.578 rounds to -0.89 GBP, remainder = 0.89 - 0.89 = 0 → OK\n\n3. **Create `test/regress/1019_py.test`**: The test harness file that runs the Python test.\n\nLook at existing Python tests like `test/regress/975_py.test` and `test/regress/975.py` for the format.\n\nThe working directory is `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-1019`.\n