        {
          "type": "tool_use",
          "name": "Bash",
          "input": {
            "command": "git add src/py_commodity.cc && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nFix #1019: comms.exchange() sets provisional precision for price commodity\n\nWhen users call comms.exchange() from Python using an Amount literal like\nledger.Amount('0.005 GBP'), the Amount constructor migrates the GBP commodity\nprecision to 3 via the normal parse path.  Unlike the P directive\n(parse_price_directive in pool.cc), this migration does not set the\nCOMMODITY_PRECISION_FROM_PRICE flag, so GBP's precision gets permanently\nlocked at 3 before the journal is read.\n\nThis causes balance failures when journal GBP amounts use 2 decimal places:\nthe expression (1/1.578 GBP) rounds to -0.887 GBP at precision 3 rather than\n-0.89 GBP at precision 2, leaving an unbalanced remainder of 0.003 GBP.\n\nFix by adding a helper (mark_price_commodity_precision) that sets\nCOMMODITY_PRECISION_FROM_PRICE on the per_unit_cost commodity after the\nexchange is recorded, mirroring what parse_price_directive does.  This marks\nthe precision as tentative so that subsequent journal parsing can override it\nwith the actual transaction amount precision.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\""
